description:
&lt;p&gt;Pathology IM&amp;T Deputy Manager Band 5, 37.5 hours&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Due to career progression of our Pathology IM&amp;T colleague there is an interesting development opportunity for a permanent, full time position working within Laboratory Medicine supporting our laboratory, phlebotomy and mortuary services.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The requirement to work across Cardiff and Vale UHB sites and supporting IT systems out of routine working hours will be discussed at interview. The Pathology IT team are the heart of the Laboratory Medicine Directorate, providing comprehensive support to the Directorate teams within Biochemistry, Cellular Pathology, Haematology and Point of Care to help maintain and develop the Directorate information systems. This opportunity is a key role in interfacing with the Directorate teams, ensuring the correct logging of support issues, investigating and testing solutions. The role involves day to day supervision of a team of (currently) 3 staff members including persona development of these team members and work load prioritisation to ensure a seamless laboratory service is provided for both primary and secondary care.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ability to speak Welsh is desirable for this post; Welsh and/or English speakers are equally welcome to apply.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Closing date: 12th November 2020&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Neil Maynard - Pathology IM&amp;T Manager&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;neil.maynard@wales.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;029 2184 2745&lt;/p&gt;
